    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "BLUES NIGHT - Jon Hines and Manitoba Hal"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Jon Hines is a Cape Breton based blues artist who's received national and international radio play across Canada, UK, and the U.S. Hines has twice been nominated for an ECMA and is a 2x winner of the Maritime to Memphis Blues Challenge and winner of Music Nova Scotia Blues Recording of the Year. Jon will be joined on stage by Shelburne's own, Manitoba Hal Brolund, an accomplished Canadian blues artist, renowned for his skills on the baritone Ukulele, who's performed at festivals worldwide, including the New York Ukulele Festival, Ukulele Hall of Fame, and numerous Canadian and international folk festivals. Join us at the Osprey where having the blues never sounded so good.</p>\n\n<style>\n    .titleTax {\n       display: none !important;\n   }\n</style>\n\n"
      }
    ],
