    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Get ready to dance at the <b>St. Patrick's Day Party with The East Enders at Devour! Studios!</b> This energetic folk rock trio from Halifax will infuse traditional pub classics with Maritime charm, turning them into foot-stomping anthems that will keep everyone moving. Join us for an unforgettable night of lively music in a vibrant cultural hub, celebrating the warmth and joy of the East Coast. Don't miss your chance to revel in the festive atmosphere and create lasting memories with friends and family! </p>\n\n<p><b>About The East Enders</b><br>\nThe East Enders are an acoustic folk rock triofrom Halifax, Nova Scotia, known for their high-energy takes on traditional Maritime folk songs. Their table-banging, foot stomping shows bring a spirit of fun that makes any event unforgettable. Matt Howard (Vocals, Bodhran), Josh Bennett (Guitar, Vocals, Stomp), Calen Kinney (Fiddle), and Iain Beaton (Fiddle) give pub classics and new favourites an East Coast flavour that fills the dance floor and captures the essence of Nova Scotia. Since forming in 2015, the band has been defined by spirited performances, in the tradition of the cheerful Maritime 'kitchen party,' their shows are as much communal celebrations as they are musical shows. </p>\n\n<p><b>About Devour! Studios</b><br>\nDevour! Studios is a dynamic cultural and culinary hub housed in a former apple warehouse, featuring a state-of-the-art teaching kitchen, event hall, and performance venue. Open year-round, it fosters creativity through various educational programming, including hosting the 16th Devour! Food Film Fest from October 19-25, 2026, in Wolfville. The Studios are also available for rent; more details are available at devourstudios.com. </p>\n\n\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
